Replaced gemini-hallucinated placeholder copy with real data sourced from
the ECP plugin README (Dannytownkins/ecommerce-conversion-psychology) and
the real mobile audit report at docs/ecp/2026-04-14-637103ed/.

Specific changes:
- Hero subhead/query: "One audit. Every insight. Research-backed." +
  "800+ classified findings across 80+ reference files from Baymard,
  NN/g, peer-reviewed journals, and FTC enforcement actions. Every
  recommendation cites its source. Every citation rated by evidence
  tier." + "Not vibes. Not best practices. Actual studies, actual
  evidence tiers, actual legal compliance."
- Hero callouts (desktop + mobile): real cluster names and finding
  titles pulled from the 2026-04-14 awdmods audit:
  - Headlines & Buttons: "Hero lacks visible promise"
  - Price & Offers: "Delivery context missing"
  - Checkout Experience: "Fitment flow consumes decisions"
- Ethics Gate section: grounded to actual compliance law stack (FTC
  enforcement, CPRA, ROSCA, GDPR, WCAG 2.1) with PASS/FAIL framing
- Audit Insight Example: now shows a real finding from the actual
  awdmods mobile audit ("Mobile hero lacks a visible promise before
  the fitment flow") with Headlines & Buttons cluster, HIGH severity,
  Gold evidence tier, Mobile device, PASS ethics badge.
- Pipeline phases renamed to match real ECP workflow:
  Reconnaissance/Pattern-Extrac./Impact-Quantify/Protocol-Issue →
  Acquire/Audit/Ethics-Gate/Priority-Path (matches the actual Audit,
  Quick-scan, Build, Compare command pipeline described in the plugin)
- Pricing tier feature lists rewritten with real ECP concepts:
  Scope/Device/Clusters/Priority-Path/Cross-page/Citations/Async-Q&A
  instead of the vague "Funnel Path Primary" / "Research Citations
  Verified" placeholders
- Footer: "One audit. Every insight. Research-backed. 800+ classified
  findings · 80+ reference files. Built on Baymard · Nielsen Norman ·
  CXL · FTC enforcement."
- Footer version stamp: v1.1.0 (real plugin version)
- Title tag: "ECP — E-Commerce Psychology Audit"

Also:
- Moved Google Fonts import from index.css (which caused postcss
  "@import must precede all other statements" errors after tailwind
  inlining) into index.html as a <link> tag, with preconnect hints
  for faster font loading

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
